To check current partition in system use command: lsblk
To create new partition in system use command: fdisk /dev/sdx
+ Type w: to exit
+ Type n: to create new partition

We could not use partition until we put file system on there
ext3, ext4
xfs
zfs
fat32

Commercial: xfs and ext4

To use partition, we need following steps:
1. fdisk
2. mkfs.ext4
3. Decide where to mount partition on
4. Create folder mkdir
5. mount
6. Verify by mount command



